oRW11AC0301` is less important than understanding the locking mechanism itself. Let me verify whether the knowledge file accurately describes what `prepareVersion` does—the source indicates it retrieves the version number from the database and sets it on the primary key class for optimistic locking, which matches the table description.\n\nFor `checkVersions`, the source confirms it validates version numbers and throws `OptimisticLockException` on mismatch, which aligns with what's documented. Now I need to examine `updateVersionsWithCheck` to see if that description is also accurate.\n\nLooking at the source, this function both checks and updates version numbers—if versions match, it increments the version number, but if they don't match, it throws `OptimisticLockException`. This matches the documentation.\n\nNow I'm noticing structural issues with the RST headings. The source document has h2-level headings like \"本項で説明する内容\" at the top, followed by \"作成手順\" as the main section, with what appear to be h3 subsections underneath like \"概要\" and \"主キークラス(ExclusiveCtrlSystemAccountContext)の作成\". I need to verify how these are actually organized in the hierarchy. I'm working through the RST heading hierarchy more carefully now. In reStructuredText, heading levels are determined by the order in which underline characters first appear, not by the character itself. So the first `=====` establishes that as the top level, then `------` becomes the next level, and any subsequent characters create their own levels. Looking at this document, I need to trace through which headings are actually at the same level versus different levels based on their underline characters and their sequence of appearance.\n\nFor the content sections, I'm identifying the four main parts: the class creation list, the overview of the creation procedure, the main key class creation, and the Action creation. These map cleanly to sections s1 through s4, which seems like the right structure. The navigatio